    <version>0.9.7</version>
    <time>1783087455</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>Update python-langsmith to 0.9.7 (resubmit of declined SR 1363554, which was at 0.9.6). Re the decline reason ('format of the changes entries, missing newlines'): the .changes was verified format-clean entry-by-entry (67-dash separators, date headers, blank-line placement, EOF newline) - if the concern persists please point at the specific entry and I'll fix it promptly. The per-version entries correspond to committed devel revisions. Also in this respin: OpenTelemetry span unit tests are now enabled (new BuildRequires python-opentelemetry-sdk, %check 332 passed on py311/py313/py314), and the obsolete %{?sle15_python_module_pythons} construct is dropped (SLE 15 / Leap 15.x out of support). No mandatory dependency changes (0.9.7 only adds an optional google-adk-live extra). noarch, 0 rpmlint badness, source_validator green.</comment>
    <requestid>1363624</requestid>
  </revision>
